commit ac4577e60a08f98bffcd5de4ccbb513703335076
Author: Brien Coffield <coffbr01@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri Aug 3 22:18:18 2012 -0500

    Fix cached zip search for events so that subsequent searches return results

    Latitude and longitude are cached for a particular zip code. They are stored
    as strings with a "|" delimiter. Splitting on that delimiter was not
    correct, and would result in splitting on the empty string. Escaping the
    pipe like so: "\\|" resolves the issue, so the second through Nth search
    for the same zip will now return event results.

Author: Brien Coffield <coffbr01@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri Aug 3 19:50:24 2012 -0500

    Handle venue search that only returns one venue.

    There was a JSONException being thrown for trying to cast a JSONObject to
    a JSONArray. This happens when there's only one venue result returned from
    last.fm. So wrap that one result in a JSONArray and continue on as normal.

    Also render the venue list better for rows that have no street address.

title: Complete event ID web service
message:
Complete event ID web service

A number of problems were present with the event service when using an ID.
The issues resolved in this submission were:
 - Begin result set column indexing by 1 instead of 0
 - Handle String prepared statement argument
 - Load jdbc driver class at runtime
 - Modify ID select query to remove erroneous single quotes

In addition to these changes, also remove old build framework artifacts
since Maven is used for the web module now instead of ant.

Change-Id: I27a02b5c2f41d5fbfd2782e09559e598a123dbec

title: Adjust the ImageTask and CachedImageTask hierarchy so they share more code.
message:
Adjust the ImageTask and CachedImageTask hierarchy so they share more code.

Push all the request code to ImageTask while leaving all the cache logic
inside CachedImageTask, so their hierarchy makes more sense.

title: Move the image task request into ImageTask and create new CachedImageTask
message:
Move the image task request into ImageTask and create new CachedImageTask

The generic image task will take care of most image requests. Lists need
special caching so subclass image task with CachedImageTask which takes
care of caching images and memory management if the images take up too much
memory
